    <!-- Process Section -->
    <section class="process-section">
        <div class="section-header">
            <h2>Our Development Process</h2>
            <p>A proven methodology for successful project delivery</p>
        </div>

        <div class="process-timeline">
            <div class="process-step">
                <div class="process-number">1</div>
                <div class="process-content">
                    <h3>Discovery & Planning</h3>
                    <p>We begin by understanding your business goals, target audience, and project requirements. Our team conducts thorough research and creates a detailed project roadmap.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="process-step">
                <div class="process-number">2</div>
                <div class="process-content">
                    <h3>Design & Prototyping</h3>
                    <p>Our designers create wireframes and interactive prototypes that visualize the user experience. We refine these designs based on your feedback until they perfectly match your vision.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="process-step">
                <div class="process-number">3</div>
                <div class="process-content">
                    <h3>Development</h3>
                    <p>Our development team brings the designs to life using the most appropriate technologies. We follow best practices for clean, maintainable code and conduct regular code reviews.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="process-step">
                <div class="process-number">4</div>
                <div class="process-content">
                    <h3>Testing & QA</h3>
                    <p>We rigorously test all aspects of your application to ensure it's bug-free, secure, and performs well across all devices and browsers.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="process-step">
                <div class="process-number">5</div>
                <div class="process-content">
                    <h3>Deployment</h3>
                    <p>Once approved, we deploy your application to your chosen hosting environment, ensuring a smooth transition and minimal downtime.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="process-step">
                <div class="process-number">6</div>
                <div class="process-content">
                    <h3>Maintenance & Support</h3>
                    <p>Our relationship doesn't end at launch. We provide ongoing maintenance, support, and updates to keep your application running smoothly and securely.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

 
    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="faq-section">
        <div class="section-header">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <p>Common questions about our web development services</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-accordion">
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <h3>How long does it take to develop a website?</h3>
                    <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>The timeline for web development varies based on the complexity of the project. A simple informational website might take 4-6 weeks, while a complex web application could take 3-6 months. During our initial consultation, we'll provide a more accurate timeline based on your specific requirements.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <h3>What is your development process?</h3>
                    <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>Our development process follows an agile methodology with six key phases: Discovery & Planning, Design & Prototyping, Development, Testing & QA, Deployment, and Maintenance & Support. This approach allows for flexibility, regular client feedback, and iterative improvements throughout the project.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <h3>How much does a website or web application cost?</h3>
                    <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>The cost depends on various factors including the complexity of features, design requirements, and the scale of the project. We offer customized quotes based on your specific needs. Contact us for a free consultation and estimate tailored to your project.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <h3>Do you provide ongoing maintenance and support?</h3>
                    <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>Yes, we offer various maintenance and support packages to keep your website or application running smoothly after launch. These include regular updates, security patches, performance optimization, content updates, and technical support.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <h3>Can you redesign my existing website?</h3>
                    <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>We specialize in website redesigns that improve both aesthetics and functionality. Our team will analyze your current website, identify areas for improvement, and develop a modern, user-friendly design that better serves your business goals.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

   
